[h3 id=RNG
 
	" RNG
	$LF
]h3
[ul 
	[li 
		" The starting RNG depends on the date and time you start the movie.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" The RNG changes whenever certain sound effects are played, whether by Mario or the background music itself (though this depends on the level). Luck can always be manipulated by either double jumping, throwing something, wall jumping, and 
		[b 
			"very frequently
		]b
		" - (though not always) by breaking a block.
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[p 
	"The RNG is currently known to affect:
	$LF
]p
[ul 
	[li 
		" The Red ? Block and Hammer Bros. movements on the world map
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" The movement of the Scuttlebugs
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" The volcano rocks in World 8-8
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" When the final cutscene in World 8-Castle 2 (Bowser Jr. throwing Dry Bowser into the pot) activates.
		$LF
	]li
]ul
